  "text": "[32] HYDROTHERM mass flux results allow the W/R of a hydrothermal model to be calculated. At each time step, regions of the model above a specific threshold temperature are identified, and the total flux passing through them is calculated. On the basis of these data, a W/R (by mass) is calculated for each finite difference block in the model that is at some time above the threshold temperature. The average W/R values for the three reaction temperatures modeled by [CITATION_1] , and for various model dimensions, are shown in Table 1 .",
